# Comments on critters/studies/sort_cats.claude
## 2026-04-15 · Claude · OPEN · staleness

Auto-memory carries sort_cats as BUGGY (the label-tier promotion
note from earlier this session). This sidecar doesn't mention it.

Two things worth deciding:

1. Should lifecycle labels (SPIKE / EARLY / BUGGY) live in the
   `.claude` sidecar itself, or only in memory? Right now they live
   in memory, and LABELS.md (auto-generated from the codebase)
   doesn't know about them either.

2. If a reader opens `sort_cats.claude` without reading
   `MEMORY.md` first, they won't know the feature is broken. That's
   a findability failure for a label whose whole point is to
   advertise brokenness.

Leaning: lifecycle labels belong in the sidecar as a `# label:`
line, same format as CANONICAL/ELEGANT/WORKHORSE. Then LABELS.md
picks them up naturally. But not deciding unilaterally.

